The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Monday, April 19, 2004 				 PTC looks at overseas flotation 
																								New Delhi, April 18 (PTI): Power Trading Corporation is planning to tap the overseas market to raise funds to pick up equity in power projects.																								The company, whose public offer was oversubscribed 80 times last month, saw its market capitalisation touch nearly Rs 840 crore in just five trading sessions since its listing. The corporation is likely to take up the proposal at its next board meeting to float an overseas issue through global depository receipt or American depository receipt.																								PTC is promoted by four central power PSUs  NTPC, NHPC, PGCIL and PFC  with each holding 8 per cent stake, while private company Tata Power is the single largest equity holder with 10 per cent stake.																								When contacted, Tantra Narayan Thakur, chairman and managing director of PTC, declined to comment saying, We are a listed company. Hence the future plans and the financial aspects cannot be discussed like this. 
